docs.lead_paragraph: THE CLIMATE OF ITALY AND PULMONARY CONSUMPTION.-Much misconception prevails with respect to the efficacy of foreign climes in cases of pulmonary consumption; and, however agreeable to the senses warm air, sunny skies, and luxuriant vegetation may seem, they afford no proof of salubrity, nor of the beneficial effect of any climate.

docs.lead_paragraph: ARREST.--On Saturday morning, officer HARVEY BALDWIN, of the Eighth Ward Police, arrested an old offender, named JOHN McKIEEIN on a charge of embezzling goods from his employer, in Hudson-street. While the officer was proceeding to the Police Court with the prisoner, he (the prisoner) communicated to him where the goods, as well as others, were to be found.

docs.lead_paragraph: Mr. JOHN O'DONOHUE, the Irish patriot, who stood in the same dock with MEAGHER and M'MANUS, and who, like his other compatriots, escaped from his place of deportation in Australia, arrived in this City from California yesterday morning. docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship Northern Light, Capt. J. MINER, arrived at this port yesterday from San Juan de Nicaragua, whence she sailed on the 17th inst. She left New-York on the 5th of July at 3 P. M., and arrived at San Juan on the 15th, at 11 A. M., stopping at Kingston for coal, which place she left at 5 P. M. on the 12th.

docs.lead_paragraph: Senator BORLAND was unable to tear himself away from his Arkansas constituency, without delivering himself of a farewell address. It is always gratifying to observe the example of WASHINGTON finding favor with living statesmen; albeit, personal, and not general and political topics, are the staple of the imitation.

docs.lead_paragraph: SHIP-BUILDING.--Mr. PATTISON has just completed a contract for building a ship of 1,000 tons burden, for Messrs. HURLBUT Co, of New-York. The keel is shortly to be laid at his yard, at the foot of North Seventh-street.

headline.main: THE BELL-RINGER AT NIAGARA.; FLIGHT THE THIRD. With an Episode on the Recent Tragedy.

docs.lead_paragraph: I have been a week at Niagara, and perhaps two or three days longer. I think I reached the Falls on a Monday; or was it on a Thursday, or a Saturday? I have lost an accurate perception of the flight of Time. I have read no newspapers.
